data.title: News from California, across the nation and world
data.meta_description: The L.A. Times is a leading source of breaking news, entertainment, sports, politics, and more for Southern California and the world.
data.text:
The updated COVID-19 vaccine could be available any day, a promising development for California and the nation amid a potent and enduring summer wave of the disease.

Lathan Norton scored from second base on an overthrow at first base as Lake Mary, Fla., rallied Sunday to beat Taiwan for Little League World Series championship.

As critics raise questions about his new project’s ethics, ‘Tiger King’s’ Eric Goode finds himself embroiled in another wild tale of exotic-animal owners.

From the Middle East to Latin America, incidents of water-related violence have been rising. New data from the Pacific Institute show 2023 was a record year.

The hit Apple TV+ series ‘Ted Lasso’ is heading toward a surprise fourth season, the L.A. Times confirmed Sunday.

DeShaun Foster knows there are plenty of people who don’t think he should be coaching UCLA football. He’s out to have the final say on the matter.

Mexico’s judges walked off the job following President Andres Manuel López Obrador’s plan to overhaul the judiciary, with judges elected not appointed.
